egano","1 tsp sumac (optional)","4 garlic cloves, unpeeled and crushed","2500 g water"]}],"id":"r117981","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-433CxZWEYPs\/XZQxutDhS3I\/AAAAAAAAcyE\/N_um02L8DT8Uqx0_l15Zia4fEmb7ql0wQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zvpUylLiNv4vSKDw.png","title":"Lamb kleftiko","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25.9 g","fat":"25.3 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"55.6 g","calories":"2359 kJ \/ 561 kcal"},"usefulItems":"kitchen towel, ceramic or glass bowl, sealable container, silicone bread mat, bowl, plastic wrap, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, aluminium foil, thermal serving bowl or plate, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Strain yoghurt overnight through a fine-mesh sieve lined with paper towel or a nut milk bag to get a thick and creamy tzatziki dip.","To make your own rice flour, place 250 g rice into mixing bowl and mill <strong>2 min\/speed 10<\/strong>. Use as needed.","You can buy psyllium husks from most supermarkets and health food stores.","To save time, you can make the pita bread 1 day in advance. Store in a sealable container in a cool, dark place. Reheat before serving, if desired.","Serve with a fresh Greek salad."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","4h","8 portions"]}